<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> the center of their <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"></L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span">, and like a couchant lion</L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> path, fi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rcely waits to leap upon</L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span">, &s;hould they e'er dare attempt to join,</L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 span"> ou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">real &s;eems terri<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">y'd but at</L>
<L>T<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">e tumour of his <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ear approach, from whence</L>
<L>We may expect they wil <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> no force</L>
<L>Again&s;t us &mdash; But I'm fo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> &s;peedy work, and</L>
<L>Gal<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ant actions. well becoming Engli&s;hmen.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>2. <HI>Ca<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">. Ch.</HI></SPEAKER>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">et us &s;trike &s;ome noble blow, and make an</L>
<L>Attempt w<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">rthy of our&s;elves, before a</L>
<L>Sickne&s;s &s;eize&punc; on our camp, or &s;luggi&s;h</L>
<L>Inactivity benumbs the &s;pirits</L>
<L>O<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> our men.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Leonatus.</SPEAKER>
<L>Tho' brave and experienced the Gallic</L>
<L>Commanders; veteran and more num'rous</L>
<L>Their forces, with all the advantages</L>
<L>On their &s;ide, of art and nature; &s;uch are</L>
<L>The office<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">s we have with us, and &s;uch</L>
<L>The &s;ev'ral corps they lead, on them I</L>
<L>Ground my eager hopes of victory, and</L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> to hazard all a &s;oldier can hold</L>
<L>Mo&s;t dear, both <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> and h<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nour, on equal</L>
<L><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ooting, in a clo&s;e engagement with our</L>
<L>Enemies. <STAGE>Wolfe, <HI>&amp;c. ri&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ng.</HI></STAGE></L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Wolfe.</SPEAKER>
<L>Gentlemen!</L>
<L>I <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">eel a mighty plea&s;ure in my mind,</L>
<L>To &s;ee the forward di&s;po&s;itions of</L>
<L>Your &s;ouls, Which I oftimes in our other</L>
<L>Leaders have ob&s;erv'd likewi&s;e, nor do the</L>
<L>Soldiers &s;eem to want th' ingredient</L>
<L>Nece&s;&s;ary for my plan &mdash;</L>
<L>This day I'll call a council, wherein I</L>
<L>Will propo&s;e (and doubt not but 'twill meet the</L>
<L>Wi&s;h'd-for approbation) that our army</L>
<L><PB N="54" REF="012729_0053_0F8BEBB6A6372078">Be e'er night embark'd in boats, with ev'ry</L>
<L>Nece&s;&s;ary di&s;p<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;ition for a</L>
<L>Battle, which boats &s;hall row &s;ome miles beyond</L>
<L>Quebec, upon the tide, and when that tide</L>
<L>Returns, then wrapt in &s;ilence, and the gloom</L>
<L>Of friendly night, we'll gently downward glide</L>
<L>Upon the &s;tream, and at the foot of that</L>
<L>Rough precipice, who&s;e top communicates</L>
<L>With Abraham's Height, we'll land un&s;een, and</L>
<L>Up the &s;tony &s;teep we'll climb, 'till we have</L>
<L>Gaind the level &s;ummit, and when Aurora</L>
<L>U&s;hers o'er the hills the car of day, all</L>
<L>Rang'd in order firm, and dread array of</L>
<L>War, we'll &s;hout her &s;uch a welcome, as &s;hall</L>
<L>Make Quebec's rocky ba&s;e to tremble! and</L>
<L>Wake each Frenchman out of his lethargic</L>
<L>Dream of vain &s;ecurity!</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Leonatus.</SPEAKER>
<L>This project &s;uits my di&s;po&s;ition well<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></L>
<L>Methinks I can already &s;ee both fronts</L>
<L>In battle join'd; and every &s;oldier</L>
<L>Pre&s;&s;ing onward to the goal of glory!</L>
<L>Now their white en&s;igns beaten down, are all</L>
<L>Be&s;tain'd with Gallic gore, and wear a purple</L>
<L>Dye! <STAGE>[recollecting him&s;elf]</STAGE>
the thought tran&s;ported me.</L>
<L>But here upon my &s;word <STAGE>[drawing]</STAGE>
I &s;wear <STAGE>[ki&s;&s;ing it]</STAGE></L>
<L>I from</L>
<L>That field will ne'er return, till victory</L>
<L>Is ours, or I'm born off with bleeding marks</L>
